OL,3,CBusinesses approve plans for a
OL,4,CCarlisle BID
OL,6,FCumberland Council and the Cumberland
OL,7,FBID Company will now implement the
OL,8,FBID, and the council's responsibility
OL,9,Fincludes collecting the levy and
OL,10,Fholding the funds in a ring-fenced
OL,11,Frevenue account on behalf of the BID
OL,12,Fbody.
OL,14,FPlans for the cash raised include
OL,15,F'developing and delivering an annual
OL,16,Fprogramme of festivals, public art,
OL,17,Fand cultural events', and developing
OL,18,Fmarketing to encourage tourism to
OL,19,FCarlisle.
